{
  "id": 5138641357373440,
  "name": "Extended lifetime shared workers",
  "summary": "This update adds a new option, `extendedLifetime: true`, to the `SharedWorker` constructor. This new option requests that the shared worker be kept alive even after all current clients have unloaded. This allows pages to perform asynchronous work that requires JavaScript after a page unloads, without needing to rely on a service worker.",
